<h2>User Home Page Instructions</h2>

<h5>User Capabilities Once Logged On:</h5>
<ul>
    <li>Once a user logs on, they will be directed to their personal home page.</li>
       <li> This personal home page looks and feels like the home page that unregistered users 
        can access in the sense of searching, but with some added features listed below:</li>
            <ul>
               
                <li>The first feature added is the “Create Case Study” link, that redirects to a form that allows the currently logged in user to create a new Case Study. </li>
                <li>The next feature is the "Create New Intervention" link that redirects to a form that allows the current user to create a new Intervention  </li>
               NOTE: All case studies and interventions will need to be approved by your instructor before other users can search for your work
                <li>Students can also edit submitted interventions and case files that have not been approved by their instructor by selecting the file and clicking its respective "edit" button</li>
                <li>Students can also view submitted interventions and case files that have been approved by their instructor by selecting the file and clicking its respective "view" button </li>
            </ul>
    </ul>